text: Proctocera senegalensis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by James Thomson in 1857, originally under the genus Clinia. It is known from the Democratic Republic of the Congo, Liberia, the Ivory Coast, Cameroon, Togo, and Senegal.BioLib.cz - Proctocera senegalensis.
